Introducing D.O.C. Volume 1!

I am excited to share that Jeff Mortensen and I will be hosting a dance on camera workshop in Toronto and Calgary (Montreal and Edmonton dates will be announced soon). 

Over 2 days, participants will learn industry terminology, gain practical experience with an SOA certified steadicam operator, and train with two Emmy nominated choreographers. 

We will be limiting the number of participants to ensure valuable education and training. 

⭐️Register now by emailing danceoncamera.series@gmail.com with your name and the city you would like to attend as the subject.⭐️

We look forward to seeing you there!

We’re excited to introduce one of the guest choreographers for ‘The Summit’, Louise Hradsky @lou.sky! 

A choreographer known for her strong leadership, years of experience, and collaborative spirit, Louise Hradsky is a creative heavyweight with a refined point of view. Originally from Western Canada, she found her home in the vibrant Vancouver film and television industry in 2006, working steadily across the globe as a performer, choreographer, and movement coach since.

As a performer, Louise landed roles in feature films like: Sucker Punch, Mirror Mirror; and Deadpool 2, and TV shows including: A Series Of Unfortunate Events, Once Upon A Time, and Hellcats. Her balance of technical athleticism and magnetic character performance also led her to Cirque Du Soleil, where Louise played the revered role of the Green Lizard in Cirque’s longest-running resident show in Las Vegas, Mystére.

In her years as a film and television choreographer, Louise has been nominated for an Emmy Award, MTV Movie and TV Award, and won a Leo Award for outstanding choreography. Her recent credits include Grease: Rise Of The Pink Ladies, Monarch: Legacy of Monsters, Yellowjackets, Pachinko (Opening Credits), The Good Doctor, To All The Boys (trilogy), A Million Little Things, The Midnight Club, and The Haunting Of Bly Manor, among others.
